## Task
Generate dynamic XML sitemaps for search engine indexing.

## Why This Matters
- Search engines discover content
- SEO ranking factor
- Index public content
- Professional web presence

## Sitemap Types

### 1. Static Sitemap
- Landing page
- Pricing page
- Legal pages
- Help center
- About page

### 2. Dynamic Sitemaps
- Public prompts
- Public collections
- User profiles
- Prompt packs

### 3. Sitemap Index
- Split large sitemaps (50k URLs max)
- Index file pointing to sub-sitemaps
- Auto-paginated generation

## Implementation

### Sitemap Route
```typescript
// src/app/sitemap.ts
export default async function sitemap(): Promise<MetadataRoute.Sitemap> {
  // Static pages
  const staticPages = [
    { url: 'https://jeffreysprompts.com', lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'weekly', priority: 1.0 },
    { url: 'https://jeffreysprompts.com/pricing', lastModified: new Date(), changeFrequency: 'monthly', priority: 0.8 },
    // ...
  ];

  // Dynamic pages - public prompts
  const prompts = await db.select({ id: userPrompts.id, updatedAt: userPrompts.updatedAt })
    .from(userPrompts)
    .where(eq(userPrompts.visibility, 'public'))
    .limit(50000);

  const promptPages = prompts.map(p => ({
    url: `https://jeffreysprompts.com/prompts/${p.id}`,
    lastModified: p.updatedAt,
    changeFrequency: 'weekly' as const,
    priority: 0.6,
  }));

  return [...staticPages, ...promptPages];
}
```

### Large Sitemap Handling
```typescript
// src/app/sitemap/[id]/route.ts
// For > 50k URLs, generate paginated sitemaps

export async function GET(req: Request, { params }) {
  const page = parseInt(params.id);
  const limit = 50000;
  const offset = page * limit;

  const prompts = await db.select()
    .from(userPrompts)
    .where(eq(userPrompts.visibility, 'public'))
    .limit(limit)
    .offset(offset);

  return new Response(generateSitemapXml(prompts), {
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/xml' }
  });
}
```

### Robots.txt
```typescript
// src/app/robots.ts
export default function robots(): MetadataRoute.Robots {
  return {
    rules: {
      userAgent: '*',
      allow: '/',
      disallow: ['/api/', '/app/', '/settings/', '/admin/'],
    },
    sitemap: 'https://jeffreysprompts.com/sitemap.xml',
  };
}
```

### Sitemap Submission
- Submit to Google Search Console
- Submit to Bing Webmaster Tools
- Auto-ping on content changes (optional)

## Files to Create
- src/app/sitemap.ts
- src/app/robots.ts
- src/app/sitemap/[id]/route.ts (for pagination)
- src/lib/seo/sitemap.ts

## Success Criteria
- Sitemap accessible at /sitemap.xml
- All public content included
- Large sites properly paginated
- Robots.txt configured
